##  [postcss-px-to-viewport](https://www.npmjs.com/package/postcss-px-to-viewport) 

****

```
{
  unitToConvert: 'px',
  viewportWidth: 320,
  unitPrecision: 5,
  propList: ['*'],
  viewportUnit: 'vw',
  fontViewportUnit: 'vw',
  selectorBlackList: [],
  minPixelValue: 1,
  mediaQuery: false,
  replace: true,
  exclude: [],
  landscape: false,
  landscapeUnit: 'vw',
  landscapeWidth: 568
}
```

## API 

|  |  |  |  |
| :-- | --- | --- | --- |
| `unitToConvert` |  px | `string` | px |
| `viewportWidth` | ,, `undefind`  | `number \| Function` | 320 |
| `unitPrecision` |  | `number` | 5 |
| `propList` |  vw  | `string[]` | ['*'] |
| `viewportUnit` |  | `string` | vw |
| `fontViewportUnit` |  | `string` | vw |
| `selectorBlackList` |  CSS  px  | `string[]` | [] |
| `minPixelValue` |  1  1  | `number` | 1 |
| `mediaQuery` |  | `boolean` | false |
| `replace` |  | `boolean` | true |
| `landscape` |  `landscapeWidth`  `@media (orientation: landscape)` | `boolean` | false |
| `landscapeUnit` |  | `string` | vw |
| `landscapeWidth` | ,,, `undefind`  | `number` | 568 |
| `exclude` |  node_modules  | `Regexp` | undefined |
| `include` |  'src/mobile'  (`include: /\/src\/mobile\//`)  | `Regexp` | undefined |

## 

- `propList` (Array)  vw 
  -  CSS 
  - "_"['_']
  - "*",. (['*position\*']  background-position-y)
  -  "!" . : ['*', '!letter-spacing'] letter-spacing
  - "!"  "_" : ['_', '!font\*'] font-size  font-weight 
- `selectorBlackList` (Array)  CSS  px 

  - 
    -  `selectorBlackList`  `['body']`   `.body-class` 
  -  CSS 
    -  `selectorBlackList`  `[/^body$/]` ,  `body`  `.body` 

- :

  - `/* px-to-viewport-ignore-next */`  
  - `/* px-to-viewport-ignore */`  

Example:

```css
/* example input: */
.class {
  /* px-to-viewport-ignore-next */
  width: 10px;
  padding: 10px;
  height: 10px; /* px-to-viewport-ignore */
  border: solid 2px #000; /* px-to-viewport-ignore */
}

/* example output: */
.class {
  width: 10px;
  padding: 3.125vw;
  height: 10px;
  border: solid 2px #000;
}
```

There are several more reasons why your pixels may not convert, the following options may affect this: `propList`, `selectorBlackList`, `minPixelValue`, `mediaQuery`, `exclude`, `include`.

##  PostCss 

**`postcss.config.js`**

```js
module.exports = {
  plugins: {
    ...
    'postcss-px-to-viewport-8-plugin': {
      viewportWidth: 1920,
      exclude: [/node_modules/],
      unitToConvert: 'px',
      ...
    }
  }
}
```

## vite 

**`vite.config.ts`**

```ts
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import postcsspxtoviewport8plugin from 'postcss-px-to-viewport-8-plugin';

export default defineConfig({
  css: {
    postcss: {
      plugins: [
        postcsspxtoviewport8plugin({
          unitToConvert: 'px',
          viewportWidth: file => {
            let num = 1920;
            if (file.indexOf('m_') !== -1) {
              num = 375;
            }
            return num;
          },
          unitPrecision: 5, // 
          propList: ['*'], // vw
          viewportUnit: 'vw', // 
          fontViewportUnit: 'vw', // 
          selectorBlackList: [], // CSSpx
          minPixelValue: 1, // 11
          mediaQuery: true, // 
          replace: true, //  
          exclude: [/node_modules\/ant-design-vue/], //  'node_modules' 
          include: [], // include
          landscape: false, //  landscapeWidth  @media (orientation: landscape)
          landscapeUnit: 'vw', // 
          landscapeWidth: 1024, // 
        }),
      ],
    },
  },
});
```

